      "value": "The paper has been folded Along the papyrus fibresly eleven times. The right side has been torn off. On the other three sides the Original cutting lines have been preserved. The left half of lines 1 to 5 is illegible due to mould. The eight lines on the recto have been written with black ink that has faded in several places. The verso contains only traces of letters at the top of the page."
