    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "The basmala is missing from the beginning of the letter, but the end is complete. The letter is dated to \u1e62afar 350 A.H. (l. 7). The writer asks the addressee to bring someone some goods (ll. 2; 4). The letter ends with a short greeting formula (l. 8) after which a space has been left blank and the letter closes with the \u1e25asbala.\n\u00a0"
